<html>
	<head>
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
		<title>BCM_SYNTAXCOLORING</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<p><font color="#000000" size="4"><strong>BCM_SYNTAXCOLORING</strong></font></p>
		<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="3" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%" bgcolor="#E6E6E6"><pre>BCM_SYNTAXCOLORING
	wParam = ( WPARAM )( BOOL )bOn;
	lParam = ( LPARAM )( BOOL )bGlobal;</pre>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>Enables or disables syntax coloring.</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				No return code defined.</li>
		</ul>
		<dl>
			<dt><em>bOn</em></dt>
			<dd>
				When this is non-zero the syntax coloring for the currently active text class 
				is turned on and it is turned off when this is zero.</dd>
			<dt><em>bGlobal</em></dt>
			<dd>
				When this is non-zero syntax coloring is turned on for all supported text 
				classes and it is turned off when this is zero.</dd>
		</dl>
	</body>
</html>
